g shot composition. Wireless LAN connection to suport smartphone operation The K-70 provides a host of wireless LAN (Wi-FI) functions to support operations using smartphones and tablets. By installing the dedicated Image Sync application, the user can remotely check the Live View image, capture still images and adjust such camera settings as aperture, shutter speed and ISO sensitivity to the desired level through the mobile device. It is even possible to download captured images on the moble device and upload them to your social networking websites. Read more Ergonomic Controls The buttons on the four-way controller are contoured for easy access even with gloved hands. The mode dials height has been optimized for ease of rotation. The PENTAX K-70 has been designed with meticulous attention to every detail to provide optimum comfort. LCD - Outdoor View Setting For comfortable use in any outdoor lighting situation, brightness of the K-70’s LCD monitor can be adjusted easily, depending on environment and live view needs. In bright sunlight you can increase the brightness to help review sharpness and composition, while in dim lighting situations such as concert and event photography your can decrease the brightness to reduce the eye strain from bright lights. LCD - Night Vision Setting This Night Vision Red-Light display function is extremely useful for Nightscape and Astro-photographers, as it prevents the pupils dilating in dark locations, thus not effecting your night vision. Navigation of the full camera menu and all its functions are accessible in Night Vision Red Light display, making the K-70 a fantastic option for night shooters and amateur Astro-photographers. This monitor is designed to assure optimum visibility in a wide range of photographic conditions and applications. K-70 & 0-GPS1 By combining the PENTAX K-70's built-in Shake Reduction System with the optional 0-GPS1, the GPS module, Electronic Compass and the cameras Shake Reduction mechanism combine to simplify astronomical photography of celestial bodies, without the requirement of an equatorial mount. Based on the latitude data obtained from GPS satellites and other affecting factors (the camera's direction and horizontal/vertical tilt) obtained by its various sensors, the O-GPS1 calculates the movement of celestial bodies, then synchronizes the movement of its image sensor with that of celestial bodies with great precision. Since it captures stars without a streaking effect even during extended exposures, you can record faint stars, which are difficult to detect with the naked eye. Ergonomic Controls LCD - Outdoor View Setting LCD - Night Vsion Setting K-70 & 0-GPS1 (function(f) {f(window.P._namespace("AplusModule"));}(function(P) {
